{"about_the_game":"<h2 class=\"bb_tag\">Overview</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">Defend portals from hordes of slimes with elemental foxes from a tabletop-style VR perspective. Recruit a colorful set of characters to help in your quest to reconnect a fragmented world over a 4 to 8 hour single-player story adventure.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3485250/extras/Icantakeyouthere.gif?t=1738781830\" /></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\">No fixed paths.</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">Slimes can climb anything, but they (usually) don't like to. You must know your enemy to build your defenses effectively. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3485250/extras/badplacement-3.gif?t=1738781830\" /></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\">No Upgrades. No  Numbers.</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">Placement is everything. Each level grants limited portal uses to bring items from your collection, and it's up to you to decide what to bring and where to put it. Every fox and item interacts differently with the game world, and you'll need to experiment to learn how to use them together.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3485250/extras/allthefoxes-short.gif?t=1738781830\" /></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\">No Problem</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">Portal Foxes TD uses simple intuitive 3D cursors. It can be played seated or standing, and all game elements can be moved and resized for maximum comfort. It can be played primarily right or left handed. It is very unlikely to cause motion sickness and never requires fast physical movements. Expect to  play until your battery dies.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p>","background":"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3485250/page_bg_generated_v6b.jpg?t=1738781830","background_raw":"https: